R 7.7
A loop and a half is when the sentinel is checked inside the loop in an if statement and the else is
the code afterwards if the sentinel hasn't been triggered... prevents processing of sentinel

boolean done = false;
while(!done){
	if(bridgeName){
		code
	}
	else
		done = true;
	if(bridgeLength){
		mLength = length * conversionFactor;
	}	
	else
		done = true;
}
System.out.println(stats);


while(true){
	if(bridgeName)
		code
	else
		break;
	if(bridgeLength)
		mLength = length * conversionFactor;
	else
		break;	
}
System.out.println(stats);

while(true){
		if(bridgeName)
		code
	else
		return null;
	if(bridgeLength)
		mLength = length * conversionFactor;
	else
		return null;	
}
System.out.println(stats);


I find the one with breaks much clearer